& [CurrentAttentionRuntimeRegistryState] is the live semantic registry for active attention
  + [registry_status] is active
  + [registry_scope] is periphery correlation corpus worker candidate
  + [active_root_frame] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_lmstudio_periphery_correlation_candidate
  + [active_frame_count] is 1
  + [suspended_frame_count] is 0
  + [closed_frame_count] is 5
  + [return_anchor] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\state\CurrentFocalPoint.sop
  + [registry_outside] is hidden activations, exact transformer attention, model weights, worker mutation authority, broad task competence, copy-exact overclaim, and unrelated Pinky worktree changes

  = must: update this state when focus materially changes
  = must: preserve return anchors before closing or suspending frames
  = must: keep the registry semantic and visible, not native-runtime or hidden-state based
  = should: stay compact enough for context-compression re-entry

& [AttentionFrame_2026_06_24_LMStudioPeripheryCorrelationCandidate] is the active semantic stack frame for the next periphery correlation worker candidate
  + [frame_id] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_lmstudio_periphery_correlation_candidate
  + [frame_state] is active
  + [parent_frame] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_lmstudio_second_corpus_queue
  + [child_frame_set] is functional_lmstudio_lane, one_minute_heartbeat, operating_loop_tick_011, periphery_correlation_prompt, capture_target, validator_profile, commit_receipt
  + [return_anchor] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\state\CurrentFocalPoint.sop
  + [frame_trace] is lmstudio_diverse_corpus_launch_queue_002.sop, evidence_review_review_013.sop, periphery_correlation_prompt_014.sop, 2026-06-24_operating_loop_tick_011.sop, and CurrentFocalPoint.sop
  + [focus_register] is inspect and optionally run corpus_periphery_correlation_014 through scratch isolation and validator gates
  + [question_register] is whether the local worker can propose correlations while preserving causal certainty as hypothesis or outside
  + [delineation_register] is inside periphery_correlation prompt packet, launch command, capture target, validator profile, and queue outside
  + [periphery_register] is broad competence outside, causal overclaim outside, hidden activation access outside, automatic launch outside, and unrelated dirty files outside
  + [operation_register] is inspect_candidate, optional_launch, capture_output, validate_output, codex_review, emit_next_tick
  + [evidence_register] is four family pass count, completed first queue, evidence_review_review_013, and operating_loop_tick_011
  + [wisdom_register] is minimum pass gate is met for limited-diverse scratch-isolated proposal work but remaining families still sharpen the lane
  + [caution_register] is four family passes still do not prove broad LM Studio competence, project-root safety, or causal reasoning reliability
  + [balance_register] is stable because the next launch remains single-candidate and validator-gated
  + [integration_register] is pending candidate inspection, optional launch, capture, validation, review, commit, and push
  + [frame_outside] is hidden model state, worker file mutation, remote claims before push, broad local-worker readiness, and unrelated workspace changes

  = must: treat this frame as current visible attention state
  = must: return clock_state, proof_state, balance_state, drive_state, next_step, and outside to CurrentFocalPoint when this focus pass closes
  = should: open child frames only when a concrete benchmark, scoring, or worker-profile pass is needed

(current_attention_runtime_registry_state) :active_root_frame: /semantic_register_set and return_anchor/ |registry_outside|
  + [active_root_frame] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_lmstudio_periphery_correlation_candidate
  + [semantic_register_set] is focus, question, delineation, periphery, operation, evidence, Wisdom, Caution, balance, and integration registers
  + [return_anchor] is CurrentFocalPoint
  |registry_outside| hidden model state, executable runtime stack, unreviewed worker authority, unrelated dirty files, and untracked cognition

/ [CurrentFocalPoint], [AttentionRuntimeRegistry], [TaskFrameLaunchQueue] -(EntersFrame)> [AttentionFrame_2026_06_24_LMStudioPeripheryCorrelationCandidate], [registry_outside]
* [semantic_register_set], [return_anchor], [frame_trace] -(SupportsReentry)> [periphery_correlation_candidate], [operating_loop_tick], [balance_register], [integration_register], [outside]
